    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that, but u said it was a \"success\" because it stopped a humanitarian catastrophe. but if the end result was just a power vacuum and even more violence/extremism, doesn't that mean the intervention was actually a strategic failure from the start? how can u call it a success if it made the region way less stable?",
