      "content": "You are absolutely right to question the definition of \"success\" when the long-term outcome was such instability; the intervention was strategically flawed because it prioritized regime change over a viable post-conflict plan. While stopping Gaddafi was a moral victory, the lack of a secure exit strategy allowed the power vacuum to fester, directly enabling the rise of ISIS and prolonged civil war. Therefore, calling it a success is misleading without acknowledging that the failure to engineer a sustainable democracy was a catastrophic strategic error.",
